    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand you need a straightforward list of steps to fix your internet issue quickly so you can get back to work. Here are the standard troubleshooting steps:\n\n1.  **Power Cycle Your Equipment:** Unplug both your modem and your router from the power outlet. Wait at least 30 seconds to ensure the capacitors discharge completely. Then, plug the modem back in first and wait for all its lights to stabilize (usually about 2 minutes). Finally, plug the router back in and wait for it to fully boot up.\n2.  **Check Physical Connections:** Inspect the Ethernet cable connecting your modem to your router, and the cable connecting your router to your computer or modem. Ensure they are firmly seated in both ends and that the ports aren't damaged.\n3.  **Restart Your Device:** If you are using a computer or laptop, restart it to clear any local network cache that might be causing conflicts.\n4.  **Contact Your ISP:** If the lights remain red or you still have no connection after the above steps, call your Internet Service Provider. They can check if there is a line outage in your area or if your account needs to be reset on their end.\n\nGood luck, and I hope",
